Levertov uses the poetic form of ‘What Were They Like?’ to emphasise the terrible loss
conict causes. The poem is written as a series of questions followed by their answers.
By grouping all of the answers into a single stanza rather than alternating between question
and response, Levertov creates a cumulative sense of loss, as images of destruction pile up
one after the other. This form also prompts the reader to reread the poem in order to
match each question to its answer, which consolidates the horric loss in the reader’s mind.
